    TreasuredSignoff:
      type: object
      description: |-
        A player's pre-scene sign-off to stake one of their treasured subjects.

        ``player_data`` is never client-writable — the viewset sets it from the
        requesting player, so a player can only sign off as themselves.
        ``treasured_subject`` must belong to one of the requesting player's own
        tenures (validated below) — a player cannot sign off on someone else's
        treasured subject.
      properties:
        id:
          type: integer
          readOnly: true
        beat:
          type: integer
        player_data:
          type: integer
          readOnly: true
        treasured_subject:
          type: integer
        granted_at:
          type: string
          format: date-time
          readOnly: true
        withdrawn_at:
          type: string
          format: date-time
          readOnly: true
          nullable: true
        active:
          type: boolean
          readOnly: true
      required:
      - active
      - beat
      - granted_at
      - id
      - player_data
      - treasured_subject
      - withdrawn_at
    TreasuredSignoffRequest:
      type: object
      description: |-
        A player's pre-scene sign-off to stake one of their treasured subjects.

        ``player_data`` is never client-writable — the viewset sets it from the
        requesting player, so a player can only sign off as themselves.
